post_text:
JMG Virtual Guest Speaker
Mr. Torrie Jackson, Jr. is a native of Jackson, MS. He earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science and a Master of Arts degree in Education Administration, both from Jackson State University. Mr. Jackson also earned a Master of Arts degree in Strategic Studies from the United States Army War College.
Mr. Jackson serves as an administrator in the Holmes County Consolidated School District. His career as an educator spans 27 years, 13 years as a classroom instructor, and 14 years as an administrator.
Mr. Jackson holds the rank of Lieutenant Colonel in the U.S. Army Reserve and is a veteran of Operation Iraq Freedom (2004). He recently commanded the 5th Logistics Civil Augmentation Program (LOGCAP) Support Battalion in Operation Spartan Shield (2018), Operation Inherent Resolve (2018), and Operation Freedom‚Äôs Sentinel (2018). He also holds the rank of Lieutenant with the Hinds County Sheriff‚Äôs Office-Reserve Division in Jackson, MS.
Mr. Jackson, his wife Dr. Debra Mays-Jackson, and two sons Cameron and Kendall currently live in Terry, MS.

Greetings Parents of Simmons Jr. Sr. High School,
Your voice has been heard, and we appreciate and value your feedback and suggestions. As a result, we have updated the schedule to reflect breaks throughout the day. Students will have the opportunity during breaks to take mental breaks, begin or complete Independent Practice, reload, take restroom breaks, etc. In response to that, we added 20-minute breaks after each block with a 30-minute lunch break.

IMPORTANT MESSAGE FROM HOLLANDALE SCHOOL DISTRICT, PLEASE READ AND PASS THIS INFORMATION ALONG.

Good evening Parents and Students of Hollandale School District,

Today the Governor had a press conference regarding school opening. In this conference he announced an executive order that affects the Hollandale School District. Below are the details of the order as it pertains to each school:
Sanders Elementary School - Classes will begin virtually, as planned, on August 5. For details concerning links, work to be completed, and start and end times, please visit www.trsanders.org.

Simmons Jr/Sr High School - In the executive order, the Governor delayed the start of school for students in grades 7-12 in Washington County, and some other counties, until August 17. We are seeking clarity from the Governor's office and MDE to see if this pertains to virtual learning. Once clarity is provided, we may start virtual learning before August 17. Please look for updates on the district's website and Facebook page. We will also do an automated call when we have more information.

Dr. Mario Willis

HSD proudly welcomes back Board Member Mrs. Mary Wise. She is the widow of late Mr. Bennie Wise and the mother of four children, including three daughters and one son. She is also the grandmother of six, and the great grandmother of six. Mrs. Wise is a long time supporter of Hollandale School District, being alumna herself with four children, also all attending Simmons High School. Serving as a Board of Trustee member since 2009, Mrs. Wise has committed countless hours serving the community of Arcola, where she has resided for over 60 years.
HSD welcomes you back for another great year!

post_text:
HSD proudly welcomes back Board of Trustee-Secretary Mrs. Dorothy Jernigan. She is the wife of Mr. AC Jernigan; the mother of two daughters, Gretchen McNeal(SV President/Branch Administrator of Guaranty Bank & Trust) and Dr. Kandice Jernigan(Principal of Matty Akins Elementary); and the grandmother of two(Tyra and Tayla).

Mrs. Jernigan is a retiree of Hollandale School District, where she was an educator for 35 years. Serving as the HSD Board of Trustee Secretary since joining in 2017, Mrs. Jernigan has committed countless hours serving the community of Hollandale, where she has resided for over 50 years. Mrs. Jernigan states, her main objective as a board member is to try and offer the students in the Hollandale School District the best education possible and keep them safe. Thank you for your commitment.

HSD welcomes you back for another great year!

post_text: The Administration and staff of Hollandale School District are deeply saddened by the passing of Board of Trustee President, Mr. Robert Steverson. We extend our deepest sympathies and sincere condolences to the entire Steverson family. Steverson was a long-time member of the Hollandale community, dedicated over 30 years teaching, a current and long-serving member of the Hollandale School District Board of Trustees. Mr. Steverson touched so many lives and was loved by many. We mourn his loss, but celebrate a life well-lived. Thank you for your genuine service, tireless dedication, and your unchanging commitment to our students, our staff members, and our community. You have changed so many lives, a great mentor to so many and you will be remembered forever. We love you and you will be forever in our hearts.

Congressman Bennie G. Thompson
April 15 at 4:09 PM ¬∑

Yesterday, it was announced that Mississippi‚Äôs schools will not reopen for the remainder of this school year due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Unfortunately, this means no prom, no senior class trips, and no commencement ceremonies for graduating seniors. Graduation day is the one day that all students dream of and work hard towards their entire life. I would like to use my social media platforms to recognize graduating high school and college seniors from the second congressional district of Mississippi. Please refer to the attached flyer for details and allow me to help celebrate your accomplishments. Class of 2020, I am very proud of you! The times may be uncertain but always keep the faith! #MS02Grads

We will continue to monitor the evolution of this virus in hopes to continue the program soon. Until such time, we appreciate your support and understanding.
